On request of the adversely affected party the appeals board may, on terms as are just, relieve a party from its final order of determination on the following grounds:
Mistake, inadvertence, surprise, or excusable neglect;
Newly discovered evidence that by due diligence could not have been discovered in time for the hearing;
Perjury or falsified evidence; or
Fraud affecting the proceedings other than perjury or falsified evidence.
